menu "ImGui"

    config IMGUI_PROFILING
        bool "Enable rendering profiling"
        default n
        help
            Instrument the ImGui rendering pipeline to collect per-stage
            timing breakdowns. When enabled, each frame records the time
            spent in ImGui::NewFrame(), ImGui::Render(), buffer clear,
            software rasterization, pixel format conversion, and LCD flush.

            The profiling data is logged to the console once per second
            via imgui_port_enable_profiling_console().

            This adds a small overhead per frame and should only be
            enabled for performance analysis builds.

endmenu
